
  <sn><md>### Aegean Civilization {.text-center}

:::.row
:::.col-12 .col-md-7
The ++Aegean Sea++ separates `Greece` from `Asia Minor`. Numerous `small and large islands` were scattered across the Aegean Sea.

An advanced urban civilization developed on these islands and along the coast of Asia Minor. This civilization is known in history as the `Aegean Civilization`.

The Aegean Civilization served as the ++preparatory stage++ for the `rise of civilization in Greece` and laid the foundation for later Greek cultural development.

The civilization declined and eventually `collapsed around 1200 BCE`.
